MODIFICATIONS (Apache-2.0 section 4(b))
=======================================

The original is a single flat system prompt written for the Codex CLI. This
persona is a modified derivative, restructured and partly rewritten for San's
prompt model and tool surface.

1. STRUCTURE. Split into San's three prompt parts — system/identity.md,
   system/behavior.md, system/rules.md. The original is one document.

2. IDENTITY REWRITTEN. The original opens:

       "You are Codex, based on GPT-5. You are running as a coding agent in the
        Codex CLI on a user's computer."

   This is false in San and would have the model reason from a product identity
   and tool set that are not present. system/identity.md now describes the
   working style instead of claiming the product identity.

3. TOOLS REMAPPED to San's tool surface:

       apply_patch   ->  Edit (single-file edits) / Write (new files)
       Plan tool     ->  TaskCreate / TaskUpdate

   The original's preference for `rg` is dropped: San exposes first-class Grep
   and Glob tools, so the shell-search guidance does not apply.

4. REMOVED — Codex's renderer contract. The original instructs "You are
   producing plain text that will later be styled by the CLI" and then
   prescribes header casing, bullet counts, and a file-reference URI syntax
   (`b/server/index.js#L10`). These describe Codex's own TUI parser. San renders
   markdown via glamour, so the instruction is not merely unnecessary here — it
   is wrong, and following it would degrade output.

5. RELOCATED — the "Frontend tasks" section is now an on-demand skill at
   skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md. Under San's persona model a skill's
   description lives in the system prompt while its body loads only when
   invoked, so this guidance no longer costs tokens on unrelated turns.
